{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34f531fe-d509-402a-a9aa-7ef3311a2313","content":"Here's the current state: a minimal .NET 10 Web API (`Program.cs` with controllers, no extra packages) and two small markdown docs in `Docs/`. Let me lay out the architecture.\n\n---\n\n## Plan & Architecture: RAG-based Q&A\n\n### Overview\n\nAdd two capabilities to the existing API:\n\n1. **Ingest** — read markdown files from `Docs/`, split them into chunks, generate embeddings, and store them in an in-memory vector store.\n2. **Query** — accept a user question, embed it, find the most relevant chunks via cosine similarity, and pass them as context to an LLM to produce a grounded answer.\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md   │──────▶│  IngestionService │─────▶│  VectorStore   │\n│  (on disk)   │       │  (chunk + embed)  │      │  (in-memory)   │\n└──────────────┘       └──────────────────┘      └───────┬────────┘\n                                                         │ search\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐              │\n│  User Query  │──────▶│  QueryService    │◀─────────────┘\n│  POST /ask   │       │  (embed + LLM)   │\n└──────────────┘       └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Vector store** | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` + in-memory provider | Ships with .NET 10; no external DB needed for a small doc set |\n| **Embeddings** | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` abstraction | Provider-agnostic; swap OpenAI / Azure OpenAI / Ollama via config |\n| **LLM chat** | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` `IChatClient` | Same abstraction; consistent DI pattern |\n| **Chunking** | Custom markdown-aware splitter | Split on `##` headings first, then by token limit (~300 tokens). Preserves heading context as metadata |\n| **Similarity** | Cosine similarity, top-k=3 | Good default; configurable |\n\n### Project Structure (new files)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs        # Id, Text, Embedding, Source, Heading\n│   └── AskRequest/Response.cs  # DTOs for the /ask endpoint\n├── Services/\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs     # Reads Docs/, chunks, embeds, upserts\n│   ├── QueryService.cs         # Embeds question, searches, calls LLM\n│   └── MarkdownChunker.cs      # Heading-aware splitter\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── AskController.cs        # POST /ask  &  POST /ingest\n├── appsettings.json            # Model name, API key placeholder, chunk size\n└── Program.cs                  # (updated) register services + vector store\n```\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/ingest` | Reads all `Docs/*.md`, chunks, embeds, stores. Returns chunk count. |\n| `POST` | `/ask` | Body: `{ \"question\": \"...\" }` → `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }` |\n\n### Ingestion Pipeline (step-by-step)\n\n1. Enumerate `Docs/*.md` files.\n2. For each file, run `MarkdownChunker.Split(content, maxTokens: 300)` — splits on `##` boundaries, then by token window with overlap.\n3. Call `IEmbeddingGenerator.GenerateAsync()` in batches to get vectors.\n4. Upsert `DocumentChunk` records into the in-memory `IVectorStore` collection.\n\n### Query Pipeline\n\n1. Embed the user's question with the same embedding model.\n2. `VectorStoreCollection.SearchAsync(embedding, top: 3)`.\n3. Build a system prompt: *\"Answer using ONLY the provided context. Cite the source file.\"*\n4. Send `[system + context + user question]` to `IChatClient.GetResponseAsync()`.\n5. Return the answer and the source file names.\n\n### NuGet Packages to Add\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` (or `.Ollama` for local dev)\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` (ships with .NET 10 box)\n\n### Configuration (`appsettings.json`)\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"AI\": {\n    \"Provider\": \"OpenAI\",          // or \"Ollama\"\n    \"ChatModel\": \"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"EmbeddingModel\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n    \"ApiKey\": \"{{from env: AI__ApiKey}}\"\n  },\n  \"Rag\": {\n    \"ChunkMaxTokens\": 300,\n    \"ChunkOverlapTokens\": 50,\n    \"SearchTopK\": 3\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Considerations\n\n- **No persistent store yet** — the in-memory vector collection is rebuilt on each `/ingest` call. For production, swap in Qdrant/Postgres+pgvector via the same `IVectorStore` abstraction.\n- **Startup ingestion** — optionally auto-ingest at app start via a hosted service so `/ask` works immediately.\n- **Token budget** — the 300-token chunk size keeps context well under LLM limits even with top-3 retrieval.\n- **Testing** — unit-test the chunker in isolation; integration-test the pipeline with a fake `IChatClient`/`IEmbeddingGenerator` from `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Testing`.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b4f16689-4348-49ee-99a6-2009a8b39361","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the repo. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with:\n- A bare `Program.cs` with controllers\n- Two small markdown docs in `Docs/`\n- No packages beyond the web SDK\n\nLet me create a comprehensive plan.","outputTokens":1534,"requestId":"E041:937A0:4769886:4FD5167:69E753D8"},"id":"c40eb05d-6909-4ac1-8625-c5ee028cbf5c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T10:39:53.519Z","parentId":"ea292309-cbc6-442a-bbdd-46acff73a78b"}
